Create design

create_design.Rd

Create design matrix for statistical analysis

create_design(
  object,
  formula = if (single_subgroup(object)) ~1 else ~0 + subgroup
)

Arguments

object

SummarizedExperiment
formula

formula with svars

Value

design matrix

Examples

file <- download_data('billing16.rnacounts.txt')
object <- read_counts(file, plot=FALSE)

#> 	Read: ~/importomicscache/datasets/billing16/billing16.rnacounts.txt
#> 		Read design (update if required!): ~/importomicscache/datasets/billing16/billing16.rnacounts.design.txt
#> 		Keep 67/58734 features: count >= 10 in at least some samples
#> 		TMM normalize and log2transform
#> 		Return object: counts(object)  = counts
#> 		               exprs(object)   = log2cpm
#> 		               weights(object) = voom weights (see plot)
#> 		               object$subgroup = subgroup values
#> 	Add PCA
#> 		Retain 67/67 features: non-zero, non-NA, and non-NaN for some sample
#> 		Run limma
create_design(object)

#>       BM E EM
#> BM_R1  1 0  0
#> BM_R2  1 0  0

#> EM_R3  0 0  1

create_design(object)
